<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1936-02-06T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1936-02-06T16:00:00-05:00" n="270" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d270">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">832.5151/814: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Brazil</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Gibson</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Rio de
                                        Janeiro</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-02-06T18:00:00-03:00">February 6, 1936—6
                                p.m.</date><lb/>[Received February 6—5:55 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>52. American interests here have received telegraph advices that
                            Export-Import Bank has formulated certain objections to frozen credits
                            agreement and has threatened to withdraw its commitments.</p>
                        <p>Should appreciate any information Department can give me for my
                            guidance.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Gibson</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>